5:
Why do you refuse to see the error
of your ways?!
8:
Cease your brigandry, withdraw
from here at once, and I will overlook
your crimes!
26:
Hehehe. That settles that. Another
case of a rampaging yokai
successfully CLOSED!
31:
Sorry about butting in like that, the
thing is we—
35:
We heard it all from the dango
vendor on the mountain pass! A
youth had undertaken the task of
fighting off a dangerous yokai!
38:
You need not even thank
us—dispatching evil yokai comes to
me as easily as breathing!
43:
...If you had at least assumed the
form of a human, I could have
turned a blind eye to you.
46:
Paaardon me? I will have you know, I
am an upstanding, morally PRISTINE
yokai!
50:
The first commandment of the Spirit
Hunt states clearly—
Suffer not a yokai to live!
54:
If you truly are not evil as you claim,
then run now!
59:
How silly! Why would I run if I have
done NOTHING wrong?!
64:
If you are yokai, then I must cut you
down. The law of the Spirit Hunt
commands me to do so!
69:
Then why are you telling her to run,
exactly?!
75:
My, my... Things are certainly getting
out of hand here. Mind if I step in?
86:
My name is Rengetsu. I belong to a
clan whose sole calling is to
exterminate yokai—we refer to it as
the Spirit Hunt.
89:
I fear I have been most
disrespectful. I had no idea you were
acquaintances of Lord Suizen...
91:
However, I merely acted in
accordance with the
commandments...
94:
Rengetsu. The commandments of
the Spirit Hunt have been abolished.
You need no longer heed them.
101:
H-how could that be?! But... My
whole life, I've been told how crucial
it is that I abide by those laws!
104:
We walk a path of cooperation with
the yokai now. The Diviners'
Commission has decreed it so.
108:
I... I had no idea of this change! Why
am I only hearing of this now?!
112:
Regardless, it would be best if you
rid your mind of the
commandments going forward.
120:
The Spirit Hunt is a tradition which
came from the West—much like the
diviners. We only recently added the
Hunt's followers to the Commission.
123:
It seems that my instructions were
not thorough enough. I apologize for
any inconvenience I have caused
you.
130:
I had no idea the commandments
were abolished. My behavior toward
you was inexcusable.
135:
Why, there is no need for such
apologies! Besides, deep in your
heart, you did not TRULY wish to hurt
me, right?
144:
Unfortunately, it seems there are still
those who cling to the old ways of
the Spirit Hunt...
147: What do you plan to do about them?
150:
A very good question...
Rengetsu. What would you have me
do?
157:
I was always skeptical of the
commandments... And I'm quite
frustrated that the elders lied to me
all this time.
160:
But... for them to be abolished so
abruptly... I don't know what to do.
163:
Well, you certainly are an honest
one, aren't you?
165:
Stella, Alk. Could I ask you to take
this young lady with you to Starview
Village?
168:
I will settle the matter here myself. 
I feel it's best to keep Rengetsu from
being involved any further.
187:
You mean those aren't just stars, but
entire worlds?!
190:
But... What am I even supposed to
do in a place like this?
193:
I mean... Whatever you want?
Nobody here's going to tell you
otherwise.
200:
S-so—just for example—I could go
shopping for stylish clothes, or go
buy some of the most popular
sweets?!
209:
I could also—theoretically—spend
the day out with friends, chatting
and talking about nothing at all?!
213:
Or, I could go see live plays? Or read
the latest romance mangas?!
217:
...Goodness, Rengetsu! You have
more worldly desires than you led
on!
222:
I just can't help wanting to indulge
myself! I know it's terribly selfish, but...
227:
Nah, it isn't. You're free to go wild.
Welcome to the group, Rengetsu.
231:
B-but I shouldn't have such desires! 
I am a swordsman of the Spirit Hunt,
after all...
234:
N-never mind! More than any of
that, I am grateful for your
hospitality.
241:
What have I gone and gotten myself
into?
What will become of me...
